## 2. Quantitative thresholds

* PSI > 0.25 — significant population shift; review SICR criteria.
* Bin stability < 0.60 — risk drivers no longer separate the population
  consistently across periods.
* Missing share > 50 % — data quality concern that may require
  expert credit judgement override (IFRS 9.B5.5.18).

## 3. Forward-looking adjustments

The drift surfaced here is **observed**, not projected. Combine with the
institution's macroeconomic scenario weights to determine whether SICR
materialises into Stage 2 / Stage 3 transitions in the next reporting
period.

